pping us from breaking out, preventing the outside from burrowing in.\n\n- Rosie\n|\nSuccess is a way of life, which progressively expands your joyfulness, happiness, and fulfillment.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nI was not an atheist. Few people really are, for that means blind faith in the strange proposition that this universe originated in a cipher and aimlessly rushes nowhere.\n\n- Bill Wilson, Alcoholics Anonymous - Big Book\n|\nWhen someone hurts you over and over, ask yourself, WHY DO YOU LET THEM?\n\n- Karen\n|\nI don’t know what I did to deserve someone as smart and beautiful as you.”'You were you. And maybe that was enough.\n\n- Michael Haley, Lost on the Edge of Forever\n|\nDarling, if I take your breath away, I will give you mine.\n\n- Donna\n|\nWords are a pretext. It is the inner bond that draws one person to another, not words.\n\n- Jalaluddin\n|\nChoice and perception are closely linked. They are unique, personal and emotional.\n\n- Fennel Hudson, A Waterside Year - Fennel's Journal - No. 2\n|\nSo much is lost, he said, in the shipwreck. What remains are fragments, and if you don't hold on to them the sea will take them too.\n\n- Rachel\n|\nWhen you trust yourself, everyone around you will trust you, too.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nShe was afraid of not being able to pull herself out of the dream world, never waking up, never knowing what really happened, never realizing her goals, her hopes, her dreams.\n\n- B. Barmanbek, Culpa Innata\n|\nBy accepting and learning to embrace the inevitable sorrows of life, we realize that we can experience a more enduring sense of happiness.\n\n- Sharon Salzberg, Real Love: The Art of Mindful Connection\n|\nThe world contained in a seed, Determined by its program.\n\n- Dejan Stojanovic, Circling: 1978-1987\n|\nDoes man think that We will not assemble his bones? Yes [We are] Able [even] to proportion his fingertips ' .Quran The Resurrection 75\n\n- Quran\n|\nWe Live Must Have A Dream , But Doesn't Means Life Is Just A Dream.\n\n- Jemmy\