tions, that is called success.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nWhen you've suffered a great deal in life, each additional pain is both unbearable and trifling.\n\n- Yann Martel, Life of Pi\n|\nLulu owns the kitchen,while Gracie owns the world.Petra Hermans\n\n- Petra\n|\nI want to change the world, and do something valuable and beautiful. I want people to remember me before I'm dead, and then more afterwards.\n\n- Russell Brand, My Booky Wook\n|\nTruth can only be found in a person's record of actions, not their list of intentions.\n\n- Suzy Kassem, Rise Up and Salute the Sun: The Writings of Suzy Kassem\n|\nI never fell. I don't care what they say. I'm still doing my job, as I see it.\n\n- Neil Gaiman, Murder Mysteries\n|\nThis was a townscape raised in the teeth of cold winds from the east; a city of winding cobbled streets and haughty pillars; a city of dark nights and candlelight, and intellect.\n\n- Alexander McCall Smith, The Sunday Philosophy Club\n|\nIn the end, it's not what we keep our children from that will save them. It's what we put into them in the first place.\n\n- Marc Parent, Believing It All: Lessons I Learned from My Children\n|\nThe sea reminds me of my finiteness, limitations, minuteness and powerlessness, because the sea is none of these.\n\n- Michael\n|\nClimate Change is a bit like our advanced societies. Too late to 'fix.' The only choice left is that we adapt to what we've created.\n\n- Shilpa\n|\nIf there was no such thing as a mirror in this world, then seeing our face ‘exactly’ would be considered a huge wonder.\n\n- Dada\n|\nAre you a female dog?''What?' Massie asked. 'Why?'\n\n- Lisi Harrison, The Clique\n|\nWhat it takes is the passion to lead and the commitment to that passion through a lifetime. A great number isn’t bad though, but doesn’t take numbers to change the world.\n\n- Israelmore Ayivor, Leaders' Frontpage: Leadership Insights from 21 Martin Luther King Jr. Thoughts\n|\nHe shrugged, '...my conscience rests easiest if I do only what I see as best in the moment...\n\n- Anihyr\n|\nThe Elven Way passes beyond the fields of the known into the forest of the unknown, illuminated by the glow of the elves.\n\n- The Silver Elves, The Elven Way: The Magical Path of the Shining Ones\n|\nA happy marriage- a love match- is something overwhelming, and overpowering.\n\n- Jude Morgan, Indiscretion\n|\nI never understood why women wanted equality in the workplace when in fact, that would be selling them short.\n\n- Jay\n|\nPamper a tomato, overfeed it, overwater it and you will get a Paris Hilton of a tomato.\n\n- Nigel Slater, Tender: Volume I: A Cook and His Vegetable Patch\n|\nThere should always be an end game, or else all you are doing is practicing for an opportunity for which you have no idea of what it is or what it will even look like.\n\n- Carlos Wallace, The Other 99 T.Y.M.E.S: Train Your Mind to Enjoy Serenity\n|\nEdward Gibbon, in his classic work on the fall of the Roman Empire, describes the Roman era's declension as a place where 'bizarreness masqueraded as creativity.\n\n- Edward Gibbon, The Decline and Fall of the Roman Empire\n|\nAnd I was very shy as a kid; if you sang me 'Happy Birthday,' I would cry. Quite shy. So the idea of being an actor, much less a model, was just out of this world.\n\n- Cody\n|\nRevived spirit, restored strength.\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Think Great: Be Great!\n|\nA goal is important, but what you become to achieve that goal is much more important.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nIn order to achieve a higher consciousness, one must get lost in love.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nDon’t have kids until you’re ready. And when you do have them, have them all the way. They aren’t like some Cadillac that you can turn back into the dealership after three years.\n\n- Carew Papritz, The Legacy Letters: his Wife, his Children, his Final Gift\n|\nIt is not because of setbacks that most entrepreneurs do not reach the finishing line, but because of a lack of willpower and motivation.\n\n- Danny\n|\nTrue freedom is in not having a master, but in making the master your slave\n\n- Bangambiki Habyarimana, The Great Pearl of Wisdom\n|\nYou Keep Looking at what you want but you can’t have it , and once you have it it will never be the same. Sign of times\n\n- Sami\n|\nAs things stand the 'intellectuals' only come out to lick the bones left over by the tyrant.\n\n- Nilantha\n|\nThe boy who expects every morning to open into a new world finds that today is like yesterday, but he believes tomorrow will be different.\n\n- Charles\n|\nIf you don’t believe your whole life has been a path leading to this one point, you’re not focused enough.” Master Sergeant Gabriel Luther Wells.\n\n- Mark Henwick, Cool Hand\n|\nWhen you live your life seeking the opinion and approval of others, you become a slave in your mind and soul to others. This is the worst form of slavery.\n\n- Bien\n|\nThe Sufi saying has it: 'God, to the bee, is something which has TWO stings!\n\n- Idries Shah, Special Illumination: The Sufi Use of Humor\n|\nWhatever you are not changing, you are choosing.\n\n- Laurie Buchanan, PhD\n|\nLet woman out of the home, let man into it, should be the aim of education. The home needs man, and the world outside needs woman.\n\n- Pearl\n|\nA nation which expects to be ignorant and free, in a state of civilization, expects that which never was and never will be.\n\n- Thomas\n|\nIf progress is not the right word for buildings or poems, what is the right way to evaluate cultural change? I suggest integrity.\n\n- Andy Crouch, Culture Making: Recovering Our Creative Calling\n|\nThe Christian Journey is not just to a place 'Heaven', it is also to a person 'Jesus'. Ephesians 4:13 says 'Till we all come to the measure of the stature of the fullness of Christ\n\n- Kingsley\n|\nIf you can't trust others, nobody will be able to trust you.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nIf you teach how best to bite; watch out, you might as well be the first victim.\n\n- Anita Ibeakanma, PRETTY FIGHTINGIRLS\n|\nWhen will money not come to one? It is when he speaks ill of others and scandalizes. Money will come to the one who has purity of mind, body and speech.\n\n- Dada\n|\nWhen you blame, you open up a world of excuses, because as long as you're looking outside, you miss the opportunity to look inside, and you continue to suffer.\n\n- Donna Quesada, Buddha in the Classroom: Zen Wisdom to Inspire Teachers\n|\nQuality is not an act, it is a habit.\n\n- Aristotle\n|\nConsider the simple hedgehog, and his neighbor, the opossum...do they waste their energy trying to throw one another into chasms when they face a common enemy, the winter? No!\n\n- Ransom Riggs, Library of Souls\n|\nThe tradition in Serbia has always been team sports - football, basketball, handball, volleyball and water polo, individual sports are not supported.\n\n- Novak\n|\nYou didn't have to go to the fireworks with him. Or - or let him fondle you.''Fondle?' Raisa raised her eyebrows, 'When did I mention fondling?\n\n- Cinda Williams Chima, The Exiled Queen\n|\nWho knows what tomorrow bringsIn a world where everyone lies...'Tupac\n\n- Raquel\n|\nWe will all have an end to this journey one day, some will have a great ending some will have it bad, but it’s the journey that they take that matters, in the end.\n\n- Zakariyya\n|\nShe would put her “naïve American optimism” toward making herself indispensable to him, and she’d win him. Because naïve American optimism beat out English cynicism any day.\n\n- Sabrina Jeffries, Married to the Viscount\n|\nMarry your friend, and you will be reasonably happy. Marry your lover, and you will be abundantly happy. Marry your soulmate, and you will be infinitely happy.\n\n- Matshona\n|\nKnow this: whenever you think of leaving, a part of you has already left. But it’s never too late to get it back.\n\n- Kamand\n|\nIf you are a parent, open doors to unknown directions to the child so he can explore. Don't make him afraid of the unknown,give him support.\n\n- Osho\n|\nThe world needs more dreamers, more peak performers, more people who aren’t content settling for mediocre. It’s time to stand up and create the future and life you love.\n\n- Michelle\n|\nNot I; I must be found;My parts, my title, and my perfect soul,Shall manifest me rightly.\n\n- William Shakespeare, Othello\n|\nNo matter what you've done for yourself or for humanity, if you can't look back on having given love and attention to your own family, what have you really accomplished?\n\n- Lee\n|\nIn the end, you will forget to love, and you will not have the ability to offend. When you have the ability to love, love and forget to offend.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nThere is no reason to look back, when there is so much good in front of you. Always keep moving forward on your roads of life!\n\n- Timothy Pina, Bullying Ben: How Benjamin Franklin Overcame Bullying\n|\nIf you help them (the crew) create good memories, they'll forget all the bad stuff\n\n- Geoff Dyer, Another Great Day at Sea: Life Aboard the USS George H.W. Bush"